               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480703-name-406" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-406" type="surname" value="FLOOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-406" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT FLOOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Tothill-street, Westminster. On 10th June I saw the prisoner and another boy in Tothill-street—I saw the other take a candlestick from Mr. Phillips's shop, and hand it to the prisoner, and they ran up Tothill-street, and down Dean-street, before I could get up to then—I lost sight of them in Dean-street—I did not see the prisoner again till 16th June, when he was in custody—I have known him for the last twelve months.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480703-name-407" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-407" type="surname" value="RAWSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480703-name-407" type="given" value="CHRISTOPHER"></interp>CHRISTOPHER RAWSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of John Phillips. I missed the candlestick on 10th June—I have the fellow to it at home.</p>
